        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-06T21:58:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I mostly validated this against https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc230366.aspx with a little help from https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb625963.aspx.\n\nThen I looked at \u003cwinnt.h\u003e and learned that the SDK actually provides all of the structures necessary to write one of these with semantic meaning instead of a binary blob. It looks like\n\nstruct {\n  SECURITY_DESCRIPTOR_RELATIVE …;\n  struct {\n    ACL …;\n    struct {\n      // This would be SYSTEM_MANDATORY_LABEL_ACE, but the DWORD SidStart field\n      // is not present. Instead, the SID is inline.\n      ACE_HEADER …;\n      ACCESS_MASK …;\n      SID …;\n    } ace[1];\n  } sacl;\n};\n\nYou’ll find the constants in \u003cwinnt.h\u003e too, and most of the rest can be populated with sizeof and offsetof.",
      "revId": "febfcaa6868acf03136a63d8e27e34295db8ea2c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
